type nuint = struct interface IFormattable interface IConvertible

Docs.summary: Native unsigned integer (32-bit in 32-bit platforms, and 64-bit on 64-bit platforms)

remarks.para: This data type is a floating point value that uses the natural size of the host architecture to store its value. On 32-bit systems, this uses T:System.UInt32 for storage and on 64-bit systems it uses T:System.UInt64 for storage.

As an optimization, the compiler and runtime have special knowledge of this data type, so while there is no dedicated set of IL instructions to deal with variable-size floating point values, the runtime will transform uses of nfloat into their native underlying representation transparently.
This type is defined in lowercase because it makes it feel like a C# data type when used in C# source code.
